When auto-generating a Git commit message for this repository, follow Conventional Commits:

<type>[optional scope]: <imperative description>

Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore
Scopes (optional): pos, stock, tenant, auth, inventory, deploy, ui, db

Rules:
- Lowercase subject after the colon; no trailing period; max 72 characters
- Imperative mood ("add X", not "added X")
- Optional body separated by a blank line — explain why, not what
- Breaking changes: type(scope)! or BREAKING CHANGE footer

Examples:
- feat(pos): add cart quantity stepper
- fix(stock): reject expired batch at checkout
- test(tenant): assert cross-tenant isolation on products
